org.daisy.common.priority

Class WrappingPriorityQueue<T,K extends T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
      • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingCollection<E>
        • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingQueue<E>
          • com.google.common.util.concurrent.ForwardingBlockingQueue<T>
            • org.daisy.common.priority.WrappingPriorityQueue<T,K>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, BlockingQueue<T>, Queue<T>

    public class WrappingPriorityQueue<T,K extends T>
extends ForwardingBlockingQueue<T>
    This class takes care of wrapping and unwrapping elements when they are added to the queue. The main restriction is that K has to be a subtype of T in order to be able to hide the actual to the forwarded queue.
